     const db = client.db(&quot;mydb&quot;);
     const collection = db.collection(&quot;product_items&quot;);
     pipeline = [
       {
         $match: { &quot;fullDocument.price&quot;: { $gte: 250 } }
       }
     ];
     // Define change stream
     const changeStream = collection.watch(pipeline);
     // start listen to changes
     changeStream.on(&quot;change&quot;, function(event) {
           collection.update({_id:fullDocument}, {$set:{fullDocument.price_lastupdate:fullDocument.price}})
     });
    });`
-  update stock_lastupdate only when the stock was changed than before: A similar change stream can be created for `stock_lastupdate`.
-  multiple insert or update, because I need too much performance: Instead of inserting/updating product items inside large array, this data model provides flexibility to insert as it will result in inserting single documents inside `product_items` collection.
- code and stock_id is unique: Taken care in the first part of queries by creating unique index on `code and stock_id`
  


